{
  "texts": [
    "Second, the AI assistance available to radiologists contained only predicted probabilities and did not include additional explanations, such as localization of pathologies, which could help radiologists more accurately interpret and, therefore, make better use of the available AI predictions.",
    "Designers of AI systems should investigate the optimal types of explanations to present and the mode of presentation while staying cautious of the increased cognitive burden that this additional information can bring.",
    "Another limitation is the lack of exploration into the impact of task granularity.",
    "The AI model generated predictions for 15 individual pathologies, some of which were interconnected and represented different levels of detail.",
    "For instance, airspace opacity encompasses pathologies such as atelectasis, edema and consolidation."
  ]
}